    "score" : 44,
    "last_activity_date" : 1483778710,
    "creation_date" : 1483778710,
    "answer_id" : 41519565,
    "question_id" : 13898057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For all others who stumble upon this thread from google, as 1st result in search for this error message:</p>\n\n<p>If you deleted bucket, to recreate in new region, <strong>do not wait \"manually\" until this background sync will be complete</strong>, instead put a small bash script to run and retry your needed bucket creation every 5 seconds or so.</p>\n\n<p>Example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>#!/bin/bash \nRESULT=2 \nuntil [  $RESULT -eq 0 ]; do\n    aws s3 mb s3://your.bucket.name --region us-west-2\n    RESULT=$?\n    sleep 5 \ndone \necho \"Bucket created!\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>it will retry the \"create bucket\" operation for you, every few seconds (depend on 'sleep' ) and as soon as it's possible - will create it for you, so no one can steal your bucket name by mistake :) </p>\n\n<p>hope it helps :)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 10173177,
      "reputation" : 452,
      "user_id" : 7512789,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a4855fd862a4298ab645b581117cf720?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Srivignesh KN",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7512789/srivignesh-kn"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 13,
    "last_activity_date" : 1488578155,
    "creation_date" : 1488578155,
    "answer_id" : 42589111,
    "question_id" : 13898057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This error usually occurs when a Bucket is deleted and a new bucket is created in the same name as the old bucket. </p>\n\n<p>I believe we would need to wait for certain amount of time until we can create a new bucket in the same name.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3229369,
      "reputation" : 8562,
      "user_id" : 2724978,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 62,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/WG8Ys.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "sigmaxf",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2724978/sigmaxf"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 12,
    "last_activity_date" : 1521506640,
    "last_edit_date" : 1521506640,
    "creation_date" : 1521356651,
    "answer_id" : 49345330,
    "question_id" : 13898057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>Simple and straightforward:</strong> Change the new bucket name or wait 1 hour.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 17258063,
      "reputation" : 21,
      "user_id" : 12496703,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/AUwvx.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "vel12171",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/12496703/vel12171"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1575732460,
    "creation_date" : 1575732460,
    "answer_id" : 59227511,
    "question_id" : 13898057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Change your bucket name or wait. I waited less than 30 minutes for mine. I did not need to change the name and I couldn't change it as I was set on it - it had to match my already existing domain name for a static website that I was looking to host. Anyway, in less than 30 minutes it was created automatically.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 28189,
      "reputation" : 52589,
      "user_id" : 75033,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 76,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/yqUcc.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "John Mee",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/75033/john-mee"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1577161901,
    "creation_date" : 1577161901,
    "answer_id" : 59463843,
    "question_id" : 13898057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You also get this message when you have more than 100 buckets in the account already.  There is a soft limit of 100 buckets.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11653603,
      "reputation" : 2370,
      "user_id" : 8534088,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/CrzSh.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Dmitriy Popov",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8534088/dmitriy-popov"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1673873924,
    "last_edit_date" : 1673873924,
    "creation_date" : 1614596603,
    "answer_id" : 66420921,
    "question_id" : 13898057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Finally, AWS now has a clear answer in their own knowledge center. See this: <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/s3-conflicting-conditional-operation/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Why am I getting the error &quot;A conflicting conditional operation is currently in progress against this resource&quot; from Amazon S3 when I try to re-create a bucket?</a>.</p>\n<p>I've just deleted a bucket (since S3 bucket names are globally unique and I need to create the same bucket in another AWS account) and my script that creates a bucket with the same name fails with the same error. So I have to be patient and wait for an hour.</p>\n<p><strong>Just as a confirmation:</strong> After around one hour, I can successfully create a bucket with the same name as the deleted bucket.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 231305,
      "reputation" : 66299,
      "user_id" : 495455,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 72,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/b0VBC.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Jeremy Thompson",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/495455/jeremy-thompson"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1622175495,
    "creation_date" : 1622175495,
    "answer_id" : 67732878,
    "question_id" : 13898057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I got the error running a Cloud Formation template.</p>\n<p>Turns out the IAM role the EC2 assumed that I was running the CFN template on didn't have permission to create S3 buckets.</p>\n<p>Either provide IAM access, or use a different IAM role by doing an <code>AWS Configure</code> or <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/security/how-to-implement-federated-api-and-cli-access-using-saml-2-0-and-ad-fs/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">programmatically assume a role</a> with necessary permission to create an S3 Bucket.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 25147539,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 18993131,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJw7dYih3UyhO3YS8CL3xUKDIfILClQYT3AEh7ZX=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "William Crossland",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/18993131/william-crossland"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1651260308,
    "creation_date" : 1651260308,
    "answer_id" : 72062839,
    "question_id" : 13898057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I ran into this. I created a bucket and then realized I created the bucket in the wrong region: us-west-2</p>\n<p>However, it should have been in us-east-1. I deleted the errored bucket and then tried to recreate it in the correct region.</p>\n<p>This command runs the bucket create command every 10 seconds (MacOS or Linux). It took a little over an hour to succeed.</p>\n<pre><code>watch -n 10 aws s3api create-bucket --bucket com.xenial.deploy.uat-us-east-1 --region us-east-1\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
